history.content:
You still have a decent chance to get into 61C next spring, so don't worry. Most lower division classes expand to let in everyone off the waitlist, and while you shouldn't take it for granted, you should stay on the waitlist and you'll likely get in. 

There are also plenty of upper division classes that don't require you to take CS 61C: to name a few, CS 188, CS 170, EE 120, etc. Most of the theory/ML related courses and most of the EE courses don't require 61C. If you have any EECS lower divs remaining (especially EE 16B) you should take those too.
